      • getOrParse

        public java.util.List<com.xceptance.xlt.nocoding.scriptItem.ScriptItem> getOrParse()
                                                                            throws java.io.IOException
        Gets the list of ScriptItems either by parsing them or from the cache.
        On the first execution, it gets the list from the parser and saves it in DATA_CACHE. Then, it gets the list out of the DATA_CACHE.
        Returns:
        A list of ScriptItems generated from the file located at getFilePath()
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - is thrown, for example, when the file is not found, or the parser encounters an error
